Coloration. In life, dorsum olive gray (
Fig. 3
) with irregular brownish olive blotches. A brownish olive stripe running from rostrum through eyes, ending at back of head, edged above by a thin yellowish stripe. Dorsal head with brownish olive bands or blotches. Four to seven round yellowish spots, arranging in one or two irregular rows from back of head and continuing along tail. Venter cream. In preservative, dorsum grey with irregular dark greyish brown blotches on forehead and body. Yellowish blotches faded to whitish marks in preservative.

